definitions.definition: Of a sheet of paper: having the sender's name, address, etc. pre-printed at the top.
(in combination) Having a head with specified characteristics.
definitions.example: a large-headed caricature of a politician

definitions.definition: (in combination) Heading in a certain direction.
To be in command of. (See also head up.)
definitions.example: Who heads the board of trustees?

definitions.definition: To come at the beginning of; to commence.
definitions.example: A group of clowns headed the procession.

definitions.definition: To strike with the head; as in soccer, to head the ball
To move in a specified direction.
To remove the head from a fish.
definitions.example: The salmon are first headed and then scaled.

definitions.definition: To originate; to spring; to have its course, as a river.

definitions.example: This kind of cabbage heads early.

definitions.definition: To form a head to; to fit or furnish with a head.
To cut off the top of; to lop off.

definitions.example: to head a drove of cattle

definitions.definition: To get in the front of, so as to hinder or stop; to oppose.
definitions.example: The wind headed the ship and made progress difficult.
